The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Sunday, October 10, 2004 

 Speaker code meet

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Calcutta, Oct. 9: Speaker Somnath Chatterjee has convened a joint meeting of the leaders, deputy leaders and whips of parties of both Houses on November 8 in New Delhi to evolve a code of conduct for ensuring effective functioning of Parliament. 

 ?I sincerely hope that the collective wisdom of the leaders will act as a guiding force in effective functioning of Parliament in the days to come,? he said, after opening the three-day 67th Conference of the Presiding Officers of Legislative Bodies in India at the Assembly. 

 Over 400 delegates, including speakers, deputy speakers and their secretaries from various states are attending. 




